import seaborn as sns
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    data['Year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['Year'], format='%Y', errors='ignore')
    ax = sns.lineplot(x='Year', y='Entity', data=data, estimator=len)
    ax.set(xlabel='Year', ylabel='Entity count')
    ax.xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.xticks(rotation=90)
    plt.title('What is the trend of disasters over time?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['Entity'] = data['Entity'].astype('category')
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    ax = sns.countplot(x='Entity', data=data)
    ax.set_xticklabels(ax.get_xticklabels(), rotation=90)
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        ax.xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.title('What is the most common type of disaster?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    data['Deaths'] = pd.to_numeric(data['Deaths'], errors='coerce')
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='Deaths', kde=True)
    plt.xlabel('Deaths')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.title('What is the distribution of deaths resulting from disasters?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
